================================================================================
1) EXECUTIVE OVERVIEW (PLAIN LANGUAGE)
================================================================================
What this project is:
- MLML is an offline, adaptive Data Structures and Algorithms tutoring platform.
- It combines a local LLM (Mistral-7B-Instruct-v0.3), local retrieval (FAISS +
  MiniLM embeddings), user-skill tracking (Elo-like ratings), and LoRA fine-tuning.

What problem it solves:
- Students need more than direct answers; they need guidance tailored to skill.
- Generic code models are often inconsistent in pedagogy and topic focus.
- Cloud-only tutoring has cost/privacy/network constraints.

Who it serves:
- Junior to advanced developers learning DSA.
- Interview preparation users.
- ML engineers iterating domain-specific instruction tuning pipelines.

What the system outputs:
- DSA explanations and/or code answers.
- Time and space complexity analysis.
- Strategy comparison guidance.
- Hint-first and Socratic style tutoring in tutor mode.
- Streaming "thinking + answer" events to the UI.

Core differentiators:
1) Offline first:
   - Model and retriever are local, no external inference API required.
2) Adaptive teaching:
   - Prompt style changes by user topic rating.
3) Retrieval grounding:
   - Answers can be grounded in curated DSA corpus chunks.
4) Continuous improvement loop:
   - Positive interactions can be exported and used for LoRA adapter updates.


