3.2 TRAINING AND DATA ENGINEERING (finetune/)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

[finetune/train_lora.py]
Purpose:
- Primary LoRA training script with single-round and multi-round schedules.

Notable engineering in this file:
1) Python 3.14 + safetensors compatibility patch:
   - replaces safe_open slice path that triggered access violation in this stack.
2) Windows WDDM memory behavior awareness:
   - comments and explicit max_memory planning to avoid CPU offload surprises.
3) LiveProgressCallback:
   - progress bar + writes progress.json for external watcher.

Default hyperparameters:
- MODEL: models/Mistral-7B-Instruct-v0.3
- seq_len 1024
- LoRA r 64, alpha 128, dropout 0.05
- target modules q/k/v/o and gate/up/down projections
- batch size 1
- grad accumulation 2
- learning rate 1e-4
- max steps 400
- warmup 40
- scheduler cosine
- save every 100, keep 3

Training implementation details:
- Converts records into chat-templated text for SFTTrainer.
- LoRA applied before trainer so trainable params remain fp32 for stability.
- frozen bf16 params cast to fp16 for tensor-core speed on target GPU class.
- optimizer adamw_torch
- gradient checkpointing enabled

Multi-round schedule:
- Round 1: 2e-4, 400, warmup 40
- Round 2: 5e-5, 150, warmup 15
- Round 3: 2e-5, 75, warmup 8

Evaluation utility:
- Fixed set of 10 DSA questions, qualitative output only.


[finetune/run_full_training.py]
Purpose:
- End-to-end orchestrator that merges datasets, asks confirmation, trains,
  runs post-eval in subprocess, updates .env adapter path.

Observed behavior mismatch:
- Header says multi-round intent, but actual train call currently runs a single
  625-step schedule in one round to reduce WDDM reload issues.


[finetune/run_seed_finetune.py]
Purpose:
