20) SYSTEM LIMITATIONS
================================================================================

1) Evaluation maturity:
- Mostly qualitative, no strong benchmark automation.

2) Data quality heterogeneity:
- Mixed curated and generic code corpora can dilute DSA specificity.

3) Runtime split storage complexity:
- SQLite for interactions and Mongo for auth increases ops burden.

4) Hardware fragility:
- Tight memory on 6GB class devices can cause loading instability.

5) Config drift:
- README/.env.example/compose/code defaults not fully synchronized.

6) Script contract drift risk:
- Some helper scripts may lag behind trainer CLI signature changes.


